# Project Context

## About This Project

**Poker Manager** — A Hebrew-language web app for managing friendly poker nights among ~8-10 regular players. Tracks games, calculates settlements, generates AI narratives, forecasts, and statistics.

- **Stack**: React 19 + TypeScript 5 (strict) + Vite 6
- **Styling**: Inline React styles + CSS variables (dark theme in `src/styles/index.css`)
- **Data**: LocalStorage (no backend/database)
- **Cloud**: GitHub Pages repo as storage via GitHub API
- **Deployment**: Vercel (auto-deploys from `main` branch)
- **Dev server**: `npm run dev` → **http://localhost:3000** (NEVER use port 3001)
- **AI**: Google Gemini API for narratives, forecasts, summaries, chronicles
- **Language**: Hebrew (RTL) — all user-facing text in Hebrew
- **Target**: Mobile-first, must also work on desktop
- **Font**: Outfit (Google Fonts, loaded in `index.html`)

## Architecture

```
src/
├── App.tsx                    # Root: routing, auth (PinLock), permission context, activity tracking
├── main.tsx                   # Entry point (renders App into #root)
├── version.ts                 # APP_VERSION constant + CHANGELOG array
├── permissions.ts             # Role system: admin | member | memberSync | viewer (PIN-based)
├── types/index.ts             # ALL TypeScript interfaces and types
├── styles/index.css           # CSS variables, dark theme, global styles
├── components/
│   ├── Navigation.tsx         # Bottom tab bar (New Game, History, Stats, Graphs, Settings)
│   ├── PinLock.tsx            # PIN entry screen with 4-digit keypad
│   └── AddExpenseModal.tsx    # Modal for shared expenses (pizza etc.) during live games
├── screens/
│   ├── NewGameScreen.tsx      # Game setup: player selection, AI forecast, pre-game teaser, period indicators
│   ├── LiveGameScreen.tsx     # Active game: rebuys, timer, voice announcements, shared expenses
│   ├── ChipEntryScreen.tsx    # End-of-game chip counting, profit calculation, triggers background AI
│   ├── GameSummaryScreen.tsx  # Post-game: results, settlements, AI summary, forecast comparison, collapsible sections
│   ├── HistoryScreen.tsx      # Completed games list with search/filter
│   ├── GameDetailsScreen.tsx  # Individual game details (legacy — not routed, GameSummaryScreen used instead)
│   ├── StatisticsScreen.tsx   # Player stats table, records, AI-generated Chronicle per player
│   ├── GraphsScreen.tsx       # Charts (Recharts): cumulative profit, head-to-head, impact analysis + AI insights
│   ├── SettingsScreen.tsx     # Tabs: Players, Game, Chips, Backup, Activity (admin), About
│   ├── TrainingScreen.tsx     # Poker training hub with category selection
│   ├── QuickTrainingScreen.tsx# Quick poker scenario drills
│   └── TrainingHandScreen.tsx # Full hand-by-hand training with AI analysis
├── database/
│   ├── storage.ts             # All LocalStorage CRUD: players, games, gamePlayers, settings, forecasts, backups, chronicles
│   ├── githubSync.ts          # GitHub API: sync data, backups, training data, activity log
│   └── embeddedToken.ts       # Obfuscated GitHub token for non-admin users (read sync + activity writes)
└── utils/
    ├── geminiAI.ts            # ALL Gemini AI: forecasts, summaries, chronicles, graph insights, comparison
    ├── calculations.ts        # Currency formatting, Hebrew dates, formatHebrewHalf, utility math
    ├── milestones.ts          # Player milestone detection (streaks, records, comebacks, etc.)
    ├── comboHistory.ts        # Recurring player combo analysis (who played together before)
    ├── activityLogger.ts      # Silent user activity tracking + device fingerprinting
    ├── sharing.ts             # Text-based game summary generation + WhatsApp sharing
    ├── pokerTraining.ts       # Training scenario generation, progress tracking, categories
    ├── tts.ts                 # Hebrew text-to-speech (browser speechSynthesis + Google Cloud TTS)
    └── validatePlayerData.ts  # Console-based data validation (window.validateAllPlayers)
```

## Game Lifecycle

```
NewGameScreen → LiveGameScreen → ChipEntryScreen → GameSummaryScreen
   (setup)        (play)          (count chips)      (results + AI)
```

1. **NewGameScreen**: Select players, choose location, generate AI forecast + teaser, set period markers
2. **LiveGameScreen**: Track rebuys, manage shared expenses, voice announcements
3. **ChipEntryScreen**: Count chips per player, calculate profits (must sum to zero), finalize game
4. **GameSummaryScreen**: View results, settlements, generate/view AI summary, forecast vs reality comparison

## Auth & Permissions

PIN-based authentication via `PinLock.tsx`. Roles stored in `sessionStorage`.

| Role | PIN | Can Do |
|------|-----|--------|
| `admin` | 2351 | Everything: games, players, settings, AI, sync, training |
| `member` | 2580 | View + manage games + add players |
| `memberSync` | 0852 | Same as member + cloud sync via embedded token |
| `viewer` | 9876 | View only + backup |

## Key Patterns

- **Hebrew RTL**: `direction: 'rtl'` on containers, all user-facing strings in Hebrew
- **Inline styles**: No CSS modules — follow existing inline style convention
- **Dark theme**: Use CSS variables (`var(--surface)`, `var(--text)`, etc.)
- **Native elements**: Use explicit hex colors for `<select>`/`<option>` on PC compatibility
- **Audio**: Shared `AudioContext` (max ~6 per page), `speechSynthesis` for Hebrew TTS
- **Zero-sum**: Game profits across all players must always sum to exactly zero
